text: Pennsauken is a township in Camden County, New Jersey, United States. It is a suburb of Philadelphia which is across the Delaware River. They are connected by the Betsy Ross Bridge. The township includes Petty's Island, a island in the Delaware River. == References == Category:Townships in New Jersey Category:Camden County, New Jersey Category:1892 establishments in the United States Category:1890s establishments in New Jersey
